                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a1">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#1r" facs="001"/>: Concluding Prayer of the Psalter, the standard version
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a2">
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                      <locus target="#1r" facs="001"/> Note of ownership, <q>“This Psalter belong to Aśaśe Gälaw. He bought it for 5 birr.”</q>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a3">
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                      <locus target="#124r" facs="124"/>: Name of owner (in blue ink): Azäzäw
                      </desc>
                      </item>

                      <item xml:id="e1">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#55v" facs="056"/>: The first word of the line that represents the midpoint of the psalms has been written with alternating red and black ink
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e2">
                      <desc>
                        Numbered quires: quires 2–13. Quire numbers appear both on the front of the first folio of a quire and on the last folio of a quire
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e3">
                      <desc>
                        words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#5v #7v #9r #10r #11v" facs="006 008 009 010 012"/>, etc.);
                        and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#50r #77r #97v #123v #127v" facs="050 077 098 124 128"/>);
                        and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#76v" facs="077"> f. 76v, line 5</locus>; <locus target="#76v" facs="077"> f. 76v, line 13</locus>);
                        erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#6r #7v #99v #123v" facs="006 008 100 124"/>);
                        text has been removed (<locus target="#70v" facs="071"/>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e4">
                      <desc>
                        The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an
                        appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long,
                        the scribe completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of
                        lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., <locus target="#23r #24v #25r" facs="023 025"/>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>

                    </list>
